        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Interpretation\n- For the 1:1 complex (ML), the apparent formation constant at 25 °C varies only modestly (Δlogβ ≲ 0.6) over I = 0–3 M, which indicates no strong monotonic ionic‑strength dependence in the aggregated SRD‑46 data.\n- For ML₂ and ML₃, the database aggregates show very large scatter (including implausible negatives when interpreted as overall β), which likely reflects mixing of different constant definitions (stepwise vs overall), differing media, and cross‑study variability. From these pooled values, a clear trend with ionic strength cannot be established.",
